WEBVTT

00:00.180 --> 00:01.616
<i>Previously on "Blood & Oil"... </i>

00:01.960 --> 00:03.372
All we got to do is ditch this tanker

00:03.397 --> 00:04.529
and we walk away clean.

00:04.554 --> 00:06.396
There's already a cash
reward for you fellas.

00:06.421 --> 00:08.225
You boys are probably
worth more than the oil.

00:08.250 --> 00:11.092
Slugs in him will match the
slug I found out at your rig.

00:11.117 --> 00:12.688
Ms. Briggs?

00:13.078 --> 00:15.202
How's my dad? Is he gonna be all right?

00:15.227 --> 00:16.573
[Chuckles] Oh, he'll be all right.

00:16.598 --> 00:17.614
[Camera shutter clicks]

00:17.665 --> 00:18.866
I'm gonna let you in.

00:18.868 --> 00:20.801
A share of this deal's gonna cost you 500k.

00:20.835 --> 00:22.036
What do you mean, you bought it?

00:22.038 --> 00:23.838
I committed to something
with Hap today, okay?

00:23.872 --> 00:24.955
Why can't we do both?

00:25.006 --> 00:26.601
Because there's not
enough money to do both.

00:26.626 --> 00:28.601
I don't think I'm gonna be able
to go in with you after all.

00:28.626 --> 00:30.761
I got to take care of some
things on the home front first.

00:30.795 --> 00:33.013
Wick: This is Jules
Jackman... my girlfriend.

00:33.047 --> 00:35.215
Hap Briggs. Twice in two days...

00:35.266 --> 00:37.050
This is starting to become a habit again.

00:38.553 --> 00:40.888
We shouldn't automatically discount anyone.

00:40.939 --> 00:44.558
No son of mine would put a gun in my face.

00:45.268 --> 00:46.434
[Gasps]

00:46.695 --> 00:48.612
[Breathing heavily]

00:48.663 --> 00:50.897
Jules: Another nightmare?

00:50.932 --> 00:52.232
Yeah, well, that's what you get

00:52.283 --> 00:53.784
for trying to kill your own father.

00:53.818 --> 00:55.369
Coward.

00:55.670 --> 00:57.804
[Gasps] [Birds chirping]

00:57.855 --> 01:00.437
[Breathing heavily]

01:01.192 --> 01:04.010
Another nightmare?

01:04.045 --> 01:05.312
[Sighs]

01:08.282 --> 01:10.300
No, it was quite the opposite, actually.

01:10.351 --> 01:11.195
[Sniffs]

01:11.220 --> 01:12.382
Oh, yeah?

01:13.271 --> 01:14.387
What was it then?

01:17.364 --> 01:20.766
Well, I could tell you...

01:22.296 --> 01:23.730
or I could just show you.

01:25.100 --> 01:27.068
[Laughs]

01:28.169 --> 01:30.720
[Birds chirping]

01:30.755 --> 01:32.272
Carla: You okay, Hap?

01:32.274 --> 01:34.992
Hap: I can't stop thinking
about that night and Wick.

01:35.017 --> 01:37.735
You were wrong. No way.

01:37.929 --> 01:41.816
No way would he have done
something like that...

01:42.078 --> 01:46.398
Steal from me and put a gun in my face.

01:46.487 --> 01:47.837
You're right.

01:47.872 --> 01:49.990
I'm sorry I ever suspected him.

01:50.024 --> 01:52.257
I got to bring him back into the fold

01:52.527 --> 01:56.031
and remind him of what
it means to be my son.

02:00.929 --> 02:02.329
[Cellphone buzzes]

02:03.853 --> 02:06.788
Goldman's coming in with the
numbers for the McCutching deal.

02:06.908 --> 02:08.407
I'll set a meeting for tonight.

02:08.695 --> 02:10.877
I think I'll ask Lacey to join us.

02:11.398 --> 02:13.780
She may as well sit in while she's home,

02:13.805 --> 02:15.671
learn a little about the business,

02:15.696 --> 02:17.831
how it works in the real world.

02:18.220 --> 02:19.852
The more Briggs, the better.

02:19.904 --> 02:22.856
♪

02:28.295 --> 02:31.547
♪ Ah-ah-ah,
ah ♪

02:31.582 --> 02:34.600
♪
ah-ah-ah-ah ♪

02:34.602 --> 02:36.602
Jules: All right, Tip?

02:36.654 --> 02:38.871
- No breakfast today? 
- Tip: Mnh-Mnh.

02:38.922 --> 02:40.340
Got a case to solve.

02:40.374 --> 02:42.342
Yeah, I heard about the dead guy.

02:42.393 --> 02:43.893
Bang, bang. Yeah, it's dangerous

02:43.944 --> 02:45.611
being an oil siphoner in the Bakken.

02:45.613 --> 02:47.413
I'll count on you to
solve this one, sheriff.

02:47.448 --> 02:48.548
[Chuckles]

02:48.550 --> 02:49.982
Murders are bad for my business.

02:50.017 --> 02:52.101
And they are even worse for mine.

02:52.152 --> 02:54.704
But trust me, whoever did this,

02:54.729 --> 02:55.979
I'll get 'em.

02:56.590 --> 02:58.224
See you.

02:58.258 --> 03:01.260
♪

03:08.568 --> 03:11.570
-- Synced and corrected by ChrisKe --
-- www.addic7ed.com --

03:15.843 --> 03:17.977
Cody: Babe, do you know where
we unpacked the hot sauce?

03:18.011 --> 03:19.578
I need to put it on my frosted flakes.

03:21.669 --> 03:22.669
Billy?

03:23.450 --> 03:24.283
Billy: Hmm?

03:24.656 --> 03:26.960
Hungry, pregnant woman... Help.

03:27.453 --> 03:29.121
[Chuckles] Sorry.

03:29.172 --> 03:30.673
I just can't stop thinking about

03:30.707 --> 03:32.258
that environmental deal with Hap.

03:32.292 --> 03:35.127
Just feels like we missed the
boat on that one, you know?

03:35.178 --> 03:36.031
No.

03:36.056 --> 03:36.973
No, you didn't.

03:37.431 --> 03:39.181
You took care of your family,

03:39.216 --> 03:40.182
you bought us this house,

03:40.217 --> 03:41.517
and you invested in your friends,

03:41.551 --> 03:43.312
and I'm really excited to go
into the restaurant business

03:43.337 --> 03:45.588
- with Kess and Ada.
- Yeah.

03:49.192 --> 03:50.810
[Sighs] Look, I just want to be able

03:50.812 --> 03:52.007
to give you everything you deserve,

03:52.032 --> 03:54.257
whether it's this house or
hot sauce for your cereal.

03:54.282 --> 03:55.315
[Chuckles]

03:55.340 --> 03:56.374
I know.

03:56.747 --> 03:58.580
And inside deals with Hap Briggs

03:58.605 --> 04:00.472
is a way I can make that happen.

04:05.158 --> 04:06.492
Good, you're here.

04:06.543 --> 04:07.793
Get that can and paint the other side.

04:07.827 --> 04:08.994
I want this tanker out of here asap.

04:08.996 --> 04:10.963
What are you talking about?

04:10.997 --> 04:12.164
We can't move anything right now.

04:12.215 --> 04:13.716
I got a buyer lined up on the reservation.

04:13.750 --> 04:15.250
I want this oil gone, and I want my money.

04:15.302 --> 04:16.969
Garry, listen to me.
There is way too much heat.

04:17.003 --> 04:18.170
Do you understand?

04:18.172 --> 04:19.305
You think I don't know this?!

04:19.339 --> 04:21.140
I should've never listened to you.

04:21.173 --> 04:22.641
Genius idea getting back at your old man

04:22.676 --> 04:23.892
- by stealing his oil.
- Hey, hey.

04:23.927 --> 04:26.312
You're the one who upped it
from grand theft to murder!

04:26.346 --> 04:28.430
- Spinks was gonna turn us in!
- And you didn't even think about

04:28.481 --> 04:30.766
offering him a piece of the profits, huh?

04:30.817 --> 04:32.929
Make him a partner instead
of killing the guy?!

04:33.953 --> 04:35.487
Listen to me.

04:35.522 --> 04:36.772
Listen to me.

04:36.823 --> 04:38.607
We're gonna sell this oil, okay?

04:38.658 --> 04:39.691
I promise you,

04:39.693 --> 04:42.161
but we have got to let things cool down.

04:42.195 --> 04:43.521
We got to be smart

04:43.546 --> 04:45.397
because the guy who's looking for us,

04:45.508 --> 04:47.876
I assure you, he is.

04:49.419 --> 04:51.203
Yeah.

04:52.288 --> 04:53.956
[Sighs] Yeah.

04:57.043 --> 04:58.427
Billy: Hard to believe, isn't it?

04:58.461 --> 05:00.345
Two weeks ago, I was
gonna open up a laundromat.

05:00.380 --> 05:01.680
I can tell you,

05:01.714 --> 05:04.550
it's a hell of a lot more fun
making profits in the millions

05:04.575 --> 05:07.443
- than it is in quarters.
- Yeah, well, I, uh...

05:07.520 --> 05:09.388
Still thinking about the one
I left out there on the table...

05:09.439 --> 05:11.000
Rock Springs response.

05:11.808 --> 05:13.425
Well, that one didn't work out

05:13.459 --> 05:14.993
quite like I thought it would.

05:14.995 --> 05:16.261
Wait, you lost money?

05:16.295 --> 05:18.096
Oh, no. No, no, no.

05:18.131 --> 05:19.097
[Chuckles]

05:19.132 --> 05:21.476
No, but I only tripled my profit on it.

05:21.567 --> 05:22.835
Wait, what do you mean?

05:23.286 --> 05:24.553
You sold it already?

05:24.587 --> 05:25.460
Oh, yeah.

05:25.485 --> 05:28.164
I flipped it to Schlumberger this morning.

05:29.726 --> 05:32.110
That's the funny thing about a boom.

05:32.145 --> 05:35.671
What goes up just... Keeps on going.

05:37.569 --> 05:38.769
Don't worry, son.

05:38.794 --> 05:40.078
You'll get yours.

05:40.103 --> 05:41.435
[Chuckles nervously]

05:41.460 --> 05:43.044
♪

05:43.069 --> 05:44.903
Wick: Jules? You okay?

05:45.018 --> 05:47.018
You've been somewhere else all morning.

05:47.043 --> 05:48.460
Yeah, just...

05:48.485 --> 05:50.486
Running through stock in my head.

05:50.511 --> 05:52.712
Think I forgot to order a
palette of old Milwaukee.

05:52.737 --> 05:54.155
Well, you'd better get on that

05:54.180 --> 05:55.981
before the roughnecks start to riot.

05:56.006 --> 05:57.256
[Chuckles]

05:57.281 --> 05:58.921
♪ Rolling over hills
and the roundabouts ♪

05:59.005 --> 06:00.505
Jules: [Sighs]

06:00.507 --> 06:02.173
Wick: Well, this is it.

06:02.224 --> 06:03.054
[Engine shuts off]

06:03.102 --> 06:06.119
Day one of the Wick
Briggs' redemption tour.

06:07.358 --> 06:08.874
Wish me luck.

06:09.382 --> 06:10.849
Um, yeah.

06:11.225 --> 06:12.858
Since when are you shy?

06:18.224 --> 06:19.107
Okay.

06:19.492 --> 06:21.359
I'll call you if I need a ride home.

06:21.410 --> 06:22.961
[Door closes]

06:24.547 --> 06:26.180
- Pop.
- Hey.

06:26.717 --> 06:28.217
That's, uh, Jules, right?

06:28.401 --> 06:30.265
Been seeing quite a lot of her.

06:30.290 --> 06:31.290
Getting serious?

06:31.765 --> 06:33.071
Yeah, I wouldn't have predicted it.

06:33.105 --> 06:35.273
I'm pretty sure it was just
a three-month booty call,

06:35.307 --> 06:36.908
but, I don't know, something changed.

06:37.660 --> 06:39.594
She gets me, you know?

06:40.937 --> 06:42.947
I'm not sure I knew what
that was like before.

06:42.982 --> 06:44.983
Well, I'm happy for you, son.

06:45.281 --> 06:47.390
Nothing better for a man than a good woman.

06:47.803 --> 06:49.137
[Sniffs]

06:49.171 --> 06:51.339
Why don't you go check
in with the tool pusher?

06:51.390 --> 06:52.507
All right.

06:52.558 --> 06:53.691
[Sniffs]

06:53.693 --> 06:55.493
[Engine turns over]

06:55.527 --> 06:58.463
♪

07:04.460 --> 07:07.429
[Engine revving]

07:10.988 --> 07:13.923
[Train whistle blowing]

07:15.556 --> 07:16.773
Woman: Hey, Sheriff Tip,

07:17.049 --> 07:18.216
we got reports of a speeding tanker

07:18.250 --> 07:19.901
on Croy Canyon Road.

07:19.935 --> 07:22.487
[Engine revving]

07:25.090 --> 07:26.474
Tip: There's that stolen tanker.

07:26.508 --> 07:27.692
[Siren wailing]

07:28.560 --> 07:29.894
Damn!

07:29.945 --> 07:31.946
[Siren wailing continues]

07:33.882 --> 07:35.516
[Tires screeching]

07:35.551 --> 07:37.652
They're headed toward the res.

07:37.686 --> 07:39.654
Star: You'd better stop him, or
we're gonna lose jurisdiction!

07:39.688 --> 07:41.572
[Wailing continues]

07:43.625 --> 07:46.093
[Tires squeal]

07:46.128 --> 07:49.947
[Siren wailing continues]

07:49.982 --> 07:51.782
Get closer! Can you see him?!

07:55.137 --> 07:57.171
Now I got you.

07:58.724 --> 08:00.558
[Tires squealing]

08:00.609 --> 08:01.726
[Both grunt]

08:01.728 --> 08:04.695
♪

08:06.000 --> 08:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

08:18.510 --> 08:19.560
[Groans]

08:19.594 --> 08:20.678
He's on the reservation!

08:20.729 --> 08:21.979
[Panting]

08:22.013 --> 08:23.264
Ugh!

08:23.315 --> 08:24.648
[Sighs]

08:32.605 --> 08:34.121
Wick: Where are we, pop?

08:34.157 --> 08:36.010
We've never been here before.

08:38.705 --> 08:40.720
Man: How you doing, Ed?

08:40.897 --> 08:42.246
[Shouting continues]

08:42.282 --> 08:44.265
Hap: I remember standing
on a parcel of land

08:44.300 --> 08:45.183
just like this one,

08:45.620 --> 08:47.786
looking out over all of our rigs.

08:47.820 --> 08:50.639
You must've asked me a thousand times,

08:50.673 --> 08:52.885
"Daddy, how do you get
that oil out of the ground?"

08:52.909 --> 08:56.156
[Chuckles] I was so damn busy back then,

08:56.692 --> 08:58.596
I... I never answered you.

09:00.495 --> 09:02.151
So, what'd you want to show me?

09:03.456 --> 09:05.020
Right there.

09:05.022 --> 09:05.987
Koala 1?

09:06.206 --> 09:08.039
You were born premature.

09:08.323 --> 09:10.525
Koala was the Incubator they had you in.

09:10.995 --> 09:12.424
And I, uh...

09:13.245 --> 09:16.263
I bought this parcel of
land the day you came home.

09:16.720 --> 09:19.522
It was always meant to be your first well.

09:22.776 --> 09:24.577
Why didn't you ever tell me that?

09:25.956 --> 09:28.892
We haven't been talking
that much lately, have we?

09:31.919 --> 09:33.853
This is the one we do together, son.

09:34.988 --> 09:36.355
[Chuckles]

09:36.390 --> 09:37.456
That all right?

09:37.481 --> 09:38.681
Yeah. [Chuckles]

09:38.784 --> 09:39.784
Yeah. [Chuckles]

09:42.847 --> 09:44.264
Ha-ha! Hey! Whoo!

09:44.596 --> 09:45.863
Now it's a party.

09:46.159 --> 09:47.409
I'm so excited for you guys!

09:47.434 --> 09:48.901
Wick: You know, once Koala hits,

09:48.903 --> 09:50.236
you're gonna have to make

09:50.287 --> 09:51.917
a very important decision, Lace.

09:51.942 --> 09:52.831
Tell me.

09:52.935 --> 09:55.333
Do you want your G650 in glossy or matte?

09:55.358 --> 09:56.292
[Laughs]

09:56.326 --> 09:57.343
[Chuckles]

09:57.635 --> 10:00.396
I wouldn't count my profits just yet.

10:01.018 --> 10:04.479
The oil business works in mysterious ways.

10:04.504 --> 10:05.667
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

10:05.692 --> 10:07.932
So, Lacey, are you excited for

10:07.957 --> 10:09.331
your first meeting at Briggs Oil?

10:09.422 --> 10:11.557
Yes, it's a dream come true, pop...

10:11.582 --> 10:13.883
A Friday evening looking
over earnings reports

10:13.908 --> 10:15.002
with old men in suits.

10:15.027 --> 10:16.331
Yes! [Laughter]

10:16.413 --> 10:17.796
Maybe you should skip it then,

10:17.798 --> 10:19.198
spend some time with your friends

10:19.223 --> 10:20.157
while you're in town.

10:20.736 --> 10:22.424
I would,

10:22.449 --> 10:25.284
but I think my father's grooming his kids

10:25.309 --> 10:27.517
to take over the business,

10:27.542 --> 10:29.292
so one meeting can't hurt.

10:29.345 --> 10:30.262
Right, Carla?

10:30.727 --> 10:32.144
[Cellphone ringing]

10:32.195 --> 10:33.312
Uh, this is Jules.

10:33.314 --> 10:34.496
I got to take this.

10:34.807 --> 10:36.415
Lacey: Oh, make sure you
tell her the good news.

10:36.466 --> 10:39.184
[Ringing continues]

10:39.235 --> 10:41.831
What? I'm in the middle of something.

10:41.856 --> 10:44.174
Gary: Good news. I unloaded the tanker.

10:44.205 --> 10:45.205
You what?

10:45.230 --> 10:48.401
50 per. Went off without a hitch.

10:48.451 --> 10:50.652
Your share comes to eight large.

10:50.750 --> 10:52.501
Look, just keep it, all right?

10:52.526 --> 10:54.844
I've got something
better going with my dad.

10:54.869 --> 10:56.486
He's bringing me into the business.

10:56.549 --> 10:57.849
What, you're going straight?

10:58.204 --> 10:59.922
Come on, man, that ain't like you.

11:00.338 --> 11:01.502
It is now.

11:01.600 --> 11:03.200
We'll talk when the money runs out.

11:04.878 --> 11:05.961
[Beep]

11:07.340 --> 11:09.074
- Hey.
- Hey.

11:09.099 --> 11:11.432
Missing the party. Yeah,
sorry. I'm done now.

11:11.457 --> 11:12.890
Let's get another drink.

11:16.089 --> 11:20.525
♪ I used to think it wasn't bad ♪

11:20.568 --> 11:22.335
Hey, Ashley, could you tell Jules I'm here?

11:22.378 --> 11:23.845
- Ashley: Sure, Cody.
- Okay, thanks.

11:23.880 --> 11:27.099
♪ I used to think that
I wouldn't go too far ♪

11:27.150 --> 11:28.940
If any of these roughnecks
give you a hard time,

11:28.965 --> 11:30.018
you just say the word.

11:30.100 --> 11:31.049
I'll take care of them for you.

11:31.178 --> 11:32.846
Uh, that's quite an offer,

11:33.060 --> 11:35.495
but I think I can take
care of myself. Thanks.

11:36.722 --> 11:39.053
I'm sorry. My mother raised me better.

11:39.078 --> 11:41.229
I'm Finn Wyler.

11:41.254 --> 11:44.123
And I told you there
were no jobs, Finn Wyler.

11:44.148 --> 11:45.732
[Chuckles] I just thought,

11:45.803 --> 11:48.771
you know, maybe if we talked
face-to-face... and now we have.

11:48.796 --> 11:50.463
And the answer's still the same.

11:50.534 --> 11:51.567
I don't need a chef.

11:52.987 --> 11:55.057
- What can I help you with, love?
- Realistic question...

11:55.082 --> 11:55.881
Why don't I cook you a meal?

11:55.979 --> 11:57.178
You're gonna love it, I promise.

11:57.213 --> 11:58.396
You don't even have a résumé!

11:58.431 --> 11:59.898
I ran a food truck in Chicago,

11:59.932 --> 12:02.317
and I swear to you, they were
lined up around the block.

12:02.368 --> 12:03.835
All right, great. Tell you what.

12:03.837 --> 12:06.190
I'll give you a call when
someone quits or needs a ride.

12:06.934 --> 12:08.518
[Chuckles] Go on. [Sighs]

12:08.543 --> 12:10.259
Get out before I stop being polite.

12:12.245 --> 12:15.697
Hey, uh, maybe you could
put in a good word for me,

12:15.731 --> 12:18.198
you know, on account of our
palpable attraction and all.

12:18.223 --> 12:20.463
Oy! [Laughs]

12:23.123 --> 12:26.559
- The boom brings all kinds.
- Ah, you don't say.

12:26.584 --> 12:28.718
So, what can I do for you?

12:29.061 --> 12:30.729
Uh, our friends, Ada and Kess...

12:30.763 --> 12:32.747
We are helping them start a restaurant,

12:32.782 --> 12:34.716
and, uh, we can't find a place.

12:34.750 --> 12:36.846
Affordable space in this town?
What you need is a miracle.

12:36.871 --> 12:39.590
Oh, well, that's why I
came to you. [Laughs]

12:39.615 --> 12:41.917
Come on, head up to the office,
and I'll see what I can do. Yes!

12:41.942 --> 12:43.709
Hap: How's your education coming?

12:43.761 --> 12:46.362
Billy: [Chuckles] Oh, you know...

12:46.780 --> 12:48.814
I'm learning how to join
pipe for the drilling rig.

12:49.854 --> 12:52.450
Of course, that's not quite
the education I had in mind.

12:52.484 --> 12:53.213
[Chuckles]

12:53.238 --> 12:55.239
Heard you and Wick have
a new play in the works.

12:55.264 --> 12:56.981
Koala, I think it's called.

12:57.139 --> 12:59.608
Listen, if you're looking to sell
any equity, I'd be interested.

12:59.806 --> 13:01.440
[Chuckles]

13:01.465 --> 13:03.483
You don't give up easy, do you, son?

13:03.508 --> 13:05.142
Well, would you?

13:05.167 --> 13:07.101
[Chuckles] Well...

13:07.126 --> 13:09.401
There's always more money
to spend on a drilling rig.

13:09.426 --> 13:10.370
That's for sure.

13:10.395 --> 13:12.893
Hell, I spend half my
time raising financing.

13:13.000 --> 13:14.690
How are those Geo reports looking?

13:16.384 --> 13:18.101
Productive.

13:19.535 --> 13:22.170
Well, maybe I could help you
cover some of the final costs,

13:22.195 --> 13:24.429
if you're open to it, sir.

13:24.717 --> 13:27.104
[Indistinct shouting in distance]

13:27.129 --> 13:28.565
Wick?!

13:28.590 --> 13:31.342
Take Billy over to Koala 1
and show him around!

13:31.593 --> 13:33.411
The new rig? Why?

13:34.470 --> 13:37.604
He's thinking about coming
on board as an investor.

13:40.999 --> 13:44.385
[Indistinct conversations]

13:44.419 --> 13:46.756
Billy: Oh, oh, wow, man!

13:47.339 --> 13:49.491
This is so much further
along than my other play.

13:49.516 --> 13:51.433
It's already pumping fluid.

13:51.910 --> 13:53.794
I mean, how much longer
till this thing's online?

13:53.829 --> 13:55.179
This isn't a guided tour, okay?

13:55.213 --> 13:56.717
You got questions, ask the tool pusher.

13:56.765 --> 13:58.358
You really don't want
me in on this, do you?

13:58.383 --> 13:59.709
You're <i> not</i> in on this.

13:59.756 --> 14:01.535
All right, this is a father/son project.

14:01.570 --> 14:02.936
Look, man,

14:02.961 --> 14:05.179
I'm not trying to come
between you and your dad.

14:05.204 --> 14:06.780
I'm here as a potential investor.

14:06.805 --> 14:07.938
That's all.

14:08.427 --> 14:09.310
I'm not your enemy.

14:09.344 --> 14:10.778
You know what else you're not?

14:10.812 --> 14:11.920
My partner.

14:11.952 --> 14:12.919
What? [Scoffs]

14:12.944 --> 14:14.479
Hey [Chuckles] wait, buddy, look,

14:14.504 --> 14:16.276
I'm trying to be cool, man.

14:16.725 --> 14:18.397
But let's be honest.

14:18.422 --> 14:20.890
I wouldn't be here if
Hap didn't want me to.

14:22.613 --> 14:23.863
I'm sorry. What are you saying?

14:24.384 --> 14:26.802
I'm saying that maybe
your problem isn't with me.

14:26.827 --> 14:27.844
It's with your dad.

14:28.246 --> 14:29.764
[Chuckles]

14:29.798 --> 14:33.133
What is this... A little frontier therapy?

14:33.185 --> 14:34.301
Look, my father and I,

14:34.352 --> 14:36.162
we've had our differences, okay, for sure,

14:36.187 --> 14:37.604
but that's behind us now,

14:37.629 --> 14:39.680
and the last thing I need is
you poking your head around,

14:39.705 --> 14:41.622
reminding him of all
the things that I'm not.

14:41.647 --> 14:43.265
Well, you don't need my help
in that department, do you?

14:43.290 --> 14:44.539
I think you remind him of what you're not

14:44.564 --> 14:45.764
all by yourself.

14:46.020 --> 14:47.137
You son of a...

14:47.162 --> 14:49.196
Get off me!

14:53.371 --> 14:54.405
[Coughs]

14:54.407 --> 14:56.209
[Coughs, breathing heavily]

14:56.234 --> 14:57.366
Wick? [Spits]

14:57.391 --> 14:59.019
Wick? Wick: Oh, God.

14:59.044 --> 15:00.127
Wick, you all right?

15:00.161 --> 15:01.178
Just get the hell out of here!

15:01.203 --> 15:02.754
Fine, man.

15:03.882 --> 15:07.084
[Inhales sharply, coughs]

15:29.670 --> 15:30.670
[Grunts]

15:30.695 --> 15:31.695
[Door opens]

15:33.234 --> 15:34.434
[Sighs]

15:34.727 --> 15:35.627
Where's Billy?

15:36.253 --> 15:38.019
What the hell happened out there?

15:39.053 --> 15:40.850
Nothing.

15:41.131 --> 15:44.587
I told you to take him out
there and show him around,

15:44.621 --> 15:47.156
not give him an MMA demonstration.

15:47.191 --> 15:49.459
You told me this was our play,

15:49.616 --> 15:50.977
that we were doing this together.

15:51.028 --> 15:52.829
We're bringing it <i> online</i> together.

15:52.863 --> 15:54.919
Capitalizing it is my department.

15:54.952 --> 15:56.739
You said this was my birthright.

15:56.764 --> 15:58.935
Shouldn't I have a say on
who's gonna be involved,

15:58.969 --> 16:00.853
- or at the very least...
- No! Hell no!

16:01.569 --> 16:03.216
You told me you wanted a second chance

16:03.241 --> 16:04.897
to prove that you could be responsible,

16:04.922 --> 16:06.856
that I could trust you!

16:07.118 --> 16:08.318
What happens?

16:11.634 --> 16:13.701
You proved anything but.

16:16.703 --> 16:17.937
So, what do you want me to do now?

16:18.096 --> 16:20.389
Now just stay out of it.

16:20.642 --> 16:22.910
[Door closes]

16:28.097 --> 16:29.764
[Sighs]

16:38.617 --> 16:40.335
Hap: Hello, Jules.

16:40.360 --> 16:43.145
[Sighs] God.

16:43.180 --> 16:44.363
You scared me.

16:44.452 --> 16:45.636
What are you doing here?

16:45.725 --> 16:46.826
I just want to talk.

16:48.494 --> 16:50.044
Yeah? About what?

16:51.204 --> 16:54.223
About what I should've
talked about four years ago.

16:56.217 --> 16:57.756
The way I treated you,

16:58.768 --> 17:00.251
it's not right.

17:01.795 --> 17:03.424
It's one of the few regrets in my life.

17:04.092 --> 17:06.520
We sneak around here for nearly two years,

17:06.858 --> 17:09.145
and then you bugger off
to New York for a month,

17:09.170 --> 17:10.715
and you come back with
a ring on your finger

17:10.741 --> 17:11.874
and Carla on your arm...

17:11.898 --> 17:15.234
No word to me, no apology
or "we should talk."

17:16.824 --> 17:18.358
I can see you're still hurt.

17:18.540 --> 17:21.042
Yeah, and I can see
you're still perceptive.

17:23.265 --> 17:24.607
I'm sorry.

17:25.465 --> 17:28.451
I-I can't make things right in a day.

17:30.381 --> 17:34.491
But I can be a very patient man,

17:35.081 --> 17:37.916
especially when something's
really important to me.

17:42.757 --> 17:44.248
Don't.

17:48.429 --> 17:49.946
Just go.

17:53.422 --> 17:54.723
Go.

17:54.748 --> 17:57.683
♪

18:00.423 --> 18:01.723
[Door opens]

18:02.189 --> 18:03.122
[Door closes]

18:03.147 --> 18:04.810
Lacey: Hey, you.

18:04.861 --> 18:06.028
Where are you headed?

18:06.079 --> 18:08.163
Hap's got me running errands in town.

18:08.197 --> 18:09.848
Well, do you want some company?

18:09.882 --> 18:11.099
Uh, I'd love for you to come,

18:11.134 --> 18:12.968
but Hap wanted this stuff
done since yesterday,

18:12.970 --> 18:14.903
so there's no time for distractions.

18:16.122 --> 18:17.756
[Engine turns over]

18:17.790 --> 18:19.436
Not even beautiful ones.

18:20.149 --> 18:21.999
I'm sorry.

18:22.161 --> 18:25.096
♪

18:39.328 --> 18:40.929
[Sizzling]

18:40.963 --> 18:42.480
[Indistinct conversations]

18:42.515 --> 18:44.266
♪ When the call hasn't come ♪

18:44.317 --> 18:49.204
♪ let me sit with you and wait ♪

18:49.238 --> 18:50.722
♪ when the other kind does ♪

18:50.773 --> 18:54.109
♪ let me help you bear the weight ♪

18:54.268 --> 18:56.420
Service here is slow.

18:56.983 --> 18:58.803
On all fronts.

18:59.600 --> 19:01.466
Yeah, well, things are...

19:01.772 --> 19:04.319
More complicated than I expected.

19:04.353 --> 19:06.121
Those photos prove nothing.

19:06.522 --> 19:08.606
There's a lot of people
that you're letting down.

19:10.194 --> 19:12.026
[Sighs]

19:12.028 --> 19:15.463
Get those soil samples
and get what we need.

19:20.202 --> 19:23.171
♪

19:30.600 --> 19:32.614
Cody: Hey, baby, it's me.

19:32.881 --> 19:34.999
Just calling to say hi and I love you.

19:35.050 --> 19:38.102
We're out looking at places
with, uh, Ada and Kess.

19:38.623 --> 19:40.321
So, I hope you're having a good day,

19:40.522 --> 19:42.206
and call me back when you can.

19:42.241 --> 19:43.291
Okay, bye. [Cellphone beeps]

19:43.764 --> 19:45.426
Not exactly sure how to say this,

19:45.461 --> 19:48.112
but, um, you and Billy,
it's... nauseating.

19:48.147 --> 19:49.731
[Chuckles] Sorry.

19:49.765 --> 19:51.633
Let me guess... High-school
sweethearts, right?

19:51.667 --> 19:52.900
Junior high, actually.

19:52.935 --> 19:54.852
We met in 7th grade... P.E. Class.

19:55.452 --> 19:56.786
Said he knew he was in love with me

19:56.811 --> 19:57.832
when I beat him in the rope climb.

19:57.857 --> 19:58.928
[Laughs]

19:59.330 --> 20:02.530
When you meet the right
guy, you just... Know.

20:04.069 --> 20:05.997
Yeah, I met that guy once.

20:06.048 --> 20:07.215
Wick?

20:07.217 --> 20:08.883
Oh, no. No, before Wick.

20:08.942 --> 20:10.543
He was older...

20:10.569 --> 20:13.504
Just sort of had this... spark

20:13.711 --> 20:14.878
like no one I'd ever met.

20:17.202 --> 20:19.591
When I was with him, nothing mattered,

20:19.616 --> 20:21.536
and then when he ended
it, nothing mattered,

20:21.561 --> 20:23.019
- and couldn't sleep and...
- Sleep or eat?

20:23.444 --> 20:24.932
Yeah.

20:25.405 --> 20:26.637
I'm sorry about that, Jules.

20:26.662 --> 20:27.752
No, no, don't be.

20:28.178 --> 20:31.342
I lost 10 pounds. I
looked fabulous. [Laughs]

20:31.940 --> 20:33.874
So, is it amazing?

20:33.909 --> 20:35.610
Oh, yes, amazing...

20:35.621 --> 20:37.155
If you don't count the busted plumbing,

20:37.180 --> 20:38.529
the leaky roof.

20:38.564 --> 20:40.147
Or the colony of rats
squatting in the kitchen.

20:40.832 --> 20:42.482
Sorry, that's the last one.

20:42.507 --> 20:44.175
Really? I mean, there's...

20:44.200 --> 20:47.002
There's got to be another
listing, right, Jules?

20:50.273 --> 20:52.508
Maybe we're coming at this the wrong way.

20:53.064 --> 20:54.608
I have an idea.

20:55.080 --> 20:56.997
[Crickets chirping]

20:57.287 --> 20:59.748
The confidential numbers from Goldman.

21:01.153 --> 21:03.204
Hap: Hey, now, look at these terms

21:03.255 --> 21:05.639
you negotiated for McCutching, Miss Carla!

21:05.690 --> 21:07.141
Carla had me shop the deal.

21:07.467 --> 21:09.043
The other bids will be in tomorrow.

21:09.077 --> 21:10.377
So, not so confidential.

21:10.553 --> 21:12.880
It'll make Goldman sharpen
their pencils a little more.

21:12.905 --> 21:15.626
Show Hap and Lacey the
projections. [Cellphone ringing]

21:15.651 --> 21:18.356
Oh, this is the foreman out at the site.

21:18.381 --> 21:20.064
Excuse me one second.

21:20.089 --> 21:21.139
Hello?

21:21.311 --> 21:22.405
Is this a bad time?

21:22.941 --> 21:25.248
Well, it was, and then you called.

21:26.444 --> 21:27.595
Is there a problem?

21:28.170 --> 21:30.014
I need to know if you
meant what you said today.

21:30.544 --> 21:32.670
I did, and I do.

21:34.684 --> 21:37.021
Are you saying you need me out there now?

21:41.945 --> 21:43.145
Yes.

21:45.878 --> 21:47.295
[Beep] [Sighs]

21:47.320 --> 21:49.070
Carla: Don't tell me you
have to go out to the site?

21:49.153 --> 21:51.168
That was the driller at McCutching.

21:51.228 --> 21:53.980
He's busted five bits on
the basalt rock. Oh, geez.

21:54.015 --> 21:55.699
Needs me out there right away.

21:55.903 --> 21:57.024
What about the meeting?

21:57.315 --> 22:00.116
I'm gonna leave it in your
capable hands, my love.

22:01.746 --> 22:02.963
See you, Matt.

22:03.241 --> 22:05.359
- You, play nice.
- All right.

22:05.384 --> 22:06.516
How long will you be?

22:06.778 --> 22:07.768
Don't wait up.

22:07.819 --> 22:09.253
♪

22:09.287 --> 22:13.724
♪ Let me escape in your arms ♪

22:13.758 --> 22:16.209
♪ baby, I'm yours ♪

22:16.736 --> 22:19.704
♪ baby, I'm yours ♪

22:21.516 --> 22:24.184
♪ love don't come easy at all ♪

22:24.235 --> 22:25.235
[Door closes]

22:25.270 --> 22:28.322
♪ I miss you so much ♪

22:28.356 --> 22:31.358
♪ I miss you so much ♪

22:33.194 --> 22:37.614
♪ tell me, is this freedom, baby? ♪

22:37.665 --> 22:40.700
♪ Chasing after danger ♪

22:40.752 --> 22:43.954
♪ making my heart race ♪

22:44.005 --> 22:45.705
♪ whoa ♪

22:45.707 --> 22:48.759
♪ maybe if the stars align ♪

22:48.793 --> 22:51.211
♪ maybe if our worlds collide ♪

22:51.213 --> 22:53.930
♪ maybe on the dark side ♪

22:53.965 --> 22:57.017
♪ we could be together, be together ♪

22:57.051 --> 22:58.135
♪

23:05.044 --> 23:06.578
[chuckles]

23:06.612 --> 23:07.813
What?

23:07.847 --> 23:09.281
Four years,

23:09.315 --> 23:12.150
and you still haven't painted that spot.

23:12.411 --> 23:15.129
- [Laughs]
- [Chuckles]

23:17.807 --> 23:19.891
I missed you.

23:19.926 --> 23:21.606
Yeah, I missed you, too.

23:22.145 --> 23:23.628
Once I stopped hating you.

23:23.679 --> 23:25.564
[Chuckles]

23:25.598 --> 23:26.865
[Sighs]

23:26.899 --> 23:28.233
Can I ask you something?

23:28.267 --> 23:30.544
Sure. Anything.

23:31.170 --> 23:33.333
What'd you tell her about
where you were going tonight?

23:34.740 --> 23:36.725
[Sighs]

23:36.776 --> 23:38.910
Out to one of the drill rigs.

23:39.059 --> 23:40.295
Mm.

23:40.723 --> 23:42.714
She was a banker, right, in New York?

23:42.748 --> 23:44.699
Mm-hmm.

23:44.734 --> 23:47.252
Word is, she modeled, too...

23:47.303 --> 23:49.036
How she put herself through Wharton.

23:49.889 --> 23:51.122
That's right.

23:51.634 --> 23:53.723
So she's basically perfect.

23:55.361 --> 23:58.463
Yes. She is.

24:00.466 --> 24:02.911
So, if you've got this
perfect wife at home,

24:04.270 --> 24:05.598
then why are you here?

24:06.505 --> 24:07.605
[Inhales deeply]

24:07.640 --> 24:10.875
Because when I lie in bed at night

24:11.200 --> 24:15.589
with my perfect wife in the perfect house

24:16.317 --> 24:19.751
with everything perfectly in place,

24:19.785 --> 24:24.348
I keep wishing that I was in a room

24:25.527 --> 24:27.611
with an unpainted spot.

24:30.424 --> 24:31.958
[Both chuckle]

24:36.678 --> 24:37.979
[Sighs]

24:38.763 --> 24:40.856
[Chuckles]

24:42.425 --> 24:43.542
[Sighs]

24:43.567 --> 24:45.209
So much for the one that got away, huh?

24:45.244 --> 24:47.562
Well, you can understand
how he feels, can't you?

24:47.613 --> 24:49.581
Wick was counting on that parcel to be his.

24:49.615 --> 24:51.466
Oh, that's a bunch of garbage, all right?

24:51.500 --> 24:53.184
Hap's taking investors in the deal.

24:53.218 --> 24:54.519
What Wick doesn't want is me.

24:54.723 --> 24:56.128
Hap's mentoring you.

24:56.153 --> 24:57.769
He's taking you under his wing.

24:57.794 --> 24:59.457
Of course his son is gonna get jealous.

24:59.508 --> 25:01.225
[Sighs] Yeah.

25:01.227 --> 25:03.073
Did you have to hit him?

25:03.098 --> 25:04.195
No! I didn't even mean to...

25:04.197 --> 25:07.598
Look, things just got a
little out of hand, okay?

25:07.633 --> 25:08.633
Look, what's getting me

25:08.661 --> 25:10.344
is what a great opportunity this is.

25:10.567 --> 25:12.046
[Sighs] Well, you always say

25:12.071 --> 25:13.838
there's no shortage of those up here.

25:13.889 --> 25:15.840
Yeah, I know I did, but
this one's different, okay?

25:15.842 --> 25:17.608
I've been out to the rig.
I've talked to the foreman.

25:17.659 --> 25:19.277
I did all the research.

25:19.497 --> 25:20.845
I mean, this parcel is drilled

25:20.879 --> 25:22.713
and ready to throw off cash from day one.

25:22.764 --> 25:24.749
Yeah, with a partner who hates you

25:24.783 --> 25:26.434
and you probably can't trust.

25:26.485 --> 25:27.958
What could possibly go wrong?

25:28.762 --> 25:30.653
So, you're saying we shouldn't invest?

25:31.747 --> 25:32.794
No.

25:33.470 --> 25:35.521
- What I'm saying is...
- [Sighs]

25:37.829 --> 25:39.966
based on everything you've told me...

25:41.136 --> 25:43.438
Kind of sounds too good to pass up.

25:45.053 --> 25:47.355
Cody LeFever, huh?

25:47.389 --> 25:49.309
Well, all right.

25:49.755 --> 25:53.341
♪

25:57.499 --> 25:59.459
Your father and I are
going to New York next week.

25:59.501 --> 26:00.317
Maybe you can come.

26:00.352 --> 26:01.385
We'll see a show.

26:06.841 --> 26:08.526
I'm making an effort here.

26:08.560 --> 26:09.894
Yeah, so am I...

26:10.153 --> 26:12.739
to not tell you exactly
what I think of your offer.

26:13.450 --> 26:15.169
What's this hostility about?

26:15.887 --> 26:17.927
Look, it's obvious I threaten you.

26:18.184 --> 26:20.538
So let me put your mind at ease.

26:21.169 --> 26:22.995
I have no intention of dropping out

26:23.020 --> 26:24.848
and working at Briggs Oil.

26:25.067 --> 26:27.987
Plus, I know how much your merger...

26:28.012 --> 26:29.559
Sorry, your marriage...

26:29.762 --> 26:30.748
Means to you.

26:31.184 --> 26:34.214
And I know how hard you
work on a nightly basis

26:34.239 --> 26:35.452
to please my father.

26:35.833 --> 26:37.419
So relax.

26:38.091 --> 26:40.044
I have no intention of messing that up.

26:45.075 --> 26:46.926
We'll have the jet come back for you...

26:46.951 --> 26:48.051
Take you to California.

26:50.044 --> 26:51.168
Careful, Carla.

26:51.313 --> 26:54.332
I don't think wine mixes
well with antidepressants.

26:56.958 --> 26:59.927
♪

27:15.093 --> 27:16.393
What are you doing?

27:16.444 --> 27:21.515
♪

27:21.549 --> 27:24.951
Amazing... a guy who's
actually more fickle than I am.

27:24.986 --> 27:27.954
♪

27:30.494 --> 27:32.452
Cody: I went home, and I did some research,

27:32.477 --> 27:33.777
and then I called Jules,

27:33.779 --> 27:36.463
and, of course, she came through.

27:37.044 --> 27:38.477
So...

27:38.776 --> 27:39.909
Here it is!

27:42.604 --> 27:45.122
I know it's not exactly
what you had in mind.

27:45.173 --> 27:47.457
But [Sighs] okay, well,
think about it, Ada, okay?

27:47.508 --> 27:50.277
There's a huge, untapped market out there.

27:50.471 --> 27:52.996
You could feed oil
workers right at the rigs.

27:52.998 --> 27:56.233
Let's say we were interested,
and we had the money ready.

27:56.267 --> 27:58.068
Then I say there's only one catch.

27:58.323 --> 27:59.727
$50,000 only gets you half.

27:59.752 --> 28:01.360
- What?!
- But the good news is,

28:01.385 --> 28:03.173
I've got the other half...

28:03.269 --> 28:04.435
Right here.

28:04.460 --> 28:05.876
Finn?

28:06.727 --> 28:09.279
Meet Finn Wyler, your new partner.

28:09.330 --> 28:11.229
Finn was a chef in Chicago.

28:11.582 --> 28:15.166
But he got a bit cocky and ended up
trading his restaurant in for this.

28:15.221 --> 28:18.154
Finn: Your recipes, me behind the grill.

28:18.429 --> 28:20.196
In a year, we could have a fleet of these.

28:22.150 --> 28:23.350
What do you say?

28:26.731 --> 28:28.331
Partners?

28:28.366 --> 28:31.301
♪

28:33.270 --> 28:35.271
[Sighs]

28:35.273 --> 28:36.239
Partners.

28:36.290 --> 28:38.041
Cody: Yes! [Laughter]

28:41.645 --> 28:44.147
[Wind whistling]

28:44.432 --> 28:46.674
Billy: Hey, Mr. Briggs,
I need to talk to you.

28:47.051 --> 28:48.084
Oh, hey. There he is.

28:48.086 --> 28:49.586
I was just about to call you

28:49.588 --> 28:51.387
and apologize for Wick's behavior.

28:52.104 --> 28:54.023
He's just like my first wife.

28:54.666 --> 28:56.258
She's down in there in Houston,

28:56.283 --> 28:59.323
making the oilmen down there
wish they were oilmen up here.

28:59.533 --> 29:00.752
What's that?

29:01.549 --> 29:03.166
Everything we've got.

29:03.424 --> 29:04.884
For Koala 1.

29:05.291 --> 29:06.669
Billy, I'm sorry.

29:06.720 --> 29:09.604
I should've been more clear.

29:10.564 --> 29:14.252
The minimum buy-in on
that piece is $500,000.

29:15.635 --> 29:17.782
We bought a house with
the money you paid me, sir.

29:17.807 --> 29:19.362
$250,000 is all we have left.

29:20.041 --> 29:21.182
Yeah.

29:21.544 --> 29:24.307
Koala 1 is almost already up and running.

29:24.588 --> 29:26.622
Why don't we just look down the road?

29:26.687 --> 29:28.487
There will be others.

29:31.168 --> 29:32.535
Billy: I'll trade you!

29:34.198 --> 29:36.580
Couple weeks back, we
partnered here on this land.

29:37.307 --> 29:39.185
Oh, I remember.

29:39.807 --> 29:43.072
I'll give you my stake here
for a share of Wick's parcel.

29:43.580 --> 29:44.791
It's a fair trade.

29:45.565 --> 29:47.932
So $250,000 in cash

29:48.464 --> 29:50.979
and your 5% stake in McCutching?

29:52.111 --> 29:54.829
You gonna tell me this
isn't worth 10 times that?

29:57.404 --> 30:00.189
You want to go all in on Koala 1?

30:01.019 --> 30:02.611
I'm all in.

30:06.026 --> 30:08.028
I'll have legal draw up the papers.

30:09.199 --> 30:10.599
There's just one thing, though.

30:10.662 --> 30:12.997
Wick... he's not gonna be
too happy about this, is he?

30:14.254 --> 30:15.363
Well...

30:16.043 --> 30:17.256
Wick's a big boy.

30:17.290 --> 30:18.624
[Chuckles]

30:18.675 --> 30:20.676
He'll just have to get over it, won't he?

30:22.012 --> 30:23.723
I mean, after all,

30:24.915 --> 30:26.733
it's just business.

30:32.145 --> 30:35.722
That was the driller.
Koala is gonna hit today.

30:35.754 --> 30:37.354
- Ah!
- Mwah!

30:37.381 --> 30:39.349
Come here! [Laughs]

30:39.400 --> 30:40.817
[Laughs]

30:40.819 --> 30:42.035
Is dad in his office? Yeah.

30:42.060 --> 30:44.261
Okay, we need to get
out to the rig right now!

30:46.390 --> 30:48.012
Hap: And you're sure it was my tanker?

30:48.037 --> 30:49.738
Tip: Oh, yeah.

30:49.763 --> 30:52.645
Logos were painted over,
but the tags matched.

30:53.567 --> 30:56.065
So, we chased the tanker,
but they got away on the res.

30:56.107 --> 30:58.275
- No jurisdiction, huh?
- Exactly.

30:59.106 --> 31:01.404
So, I got my deputy
checking the traffic cams,

31:01.438 --> 31:03.673
but, uh, here's the thing, Hap.

31:03.675 --> 31:07.777
Whoever stole your tanker
also murdered Clay Spinks.

31:09.035 --> 31:11.160
Sounds like a win-win to me, sheriff.

31:11.515 --> 31:12.949
You I.D. the driver.

31:12.983 --> 31:15.118
I get my tanker. You get your killer.

31:15.637 --> 31:16.886
All right. I'll see you.

31:16.937 --> 31:18.554
Thanks.

31:22.626 --> 31:24.427
[Sighs]

31:24.478 --> 31:28.030
♪

31:28.055 --> 31:29.722
Man: Less than 60 feet, boss!

31:29.750 --> 31:31.934
Basalt's breaking up!

31:31.969 --> 31:33.636
Keep digging!

31:34.438 --> 31:36.172
It's holding. It looks good.

31:36.206 --> 31:37.306
It's all set.

31:37.341 --> 31:39.442
30 feet till we hit, Mr. Briggs!

31:40.737 --> 31:42.371
We're getting close, Hap.

31:42.413 --> 31:44.313
Hey, Pop, Carla.

31:44.348 --> 31:46.616
- You guys remember Jules, right?
- Of course.

31:46.650 --> 31:49.160
So nice of you to come
out and support your man.

31:49.185 --> 31:50.769
Wouldn't miss it.

31:52.512 --> 31:53.679
This is amazing, isn't it?

31:53.713 --> 31:55.464
It's not just a start-up like McCutching.

31:55.498 --> 31:57.067
I mean, this is... This
is actually happening.

31:57.092 --> 31:58.403
It's like out of a movie.

31:58.428 --> 31:59.613
[Sighs] And it's ours.

31:59.638 --> 32:00.654
Wow.

32:01.323 --> 32:03.073
Woman: I know, right?

32:03.098 --> 32:04.532
Let's go say hi to your partners.

32:04.557 --> 32:06.358
[Both chuckle]

32:06.383 --> 32:07.433
Hi! Hi.

32:07.458 --> 32:08.992
- Very exciting, isn't it?
- Yeah.

32:09.017 --> 32:10.718
This must be your first oil strike.

32:10.743 --> 32:12.465
Sure beats the hell out of a
rig fire, though, doesn't it?

32:12.490 --> 32:14.290
[Chuckles] Hap: Sure does.

32:14.315 --> 32:16.717
Are you two ready for the
first day of your new life?

32:16.742 --> 32:18.126
We'll see. [Chuckles]

32:21.751 --> 32:23.852
Wick: Hey, man, I'm
sorry about the other day.

32:23.877 --> 32:26.528
Sometimes I... Speak
before I think... hit, too.

32:26.553 --> 32:27.686
It's a bad habit.

32:27.711 --> 32:30.563
Hey, listen, my bad habits
are a hell of a lot worse.

32:30.814 --> 32:32.031
[Laughs]

32:32.056 --> 32:34.356
[Chuckles]

32:34.685 --> 32:36.402
Hey, you want to go see the control room,

32:36.427 --> 32:37.393
see where all the magic happens?

32:37.418 --> 32:38.835
Sure.

32:38.958 --> 32:40.541
Uh, yeah, actually, if
you'll excuse us, too,

32:40.543 --> 32:43.177
I want to go show Billy our new food truck.

32:43.212 --> 32:45.647
He's not the only smart
investor in the family. Oh.

32:45.672 --> 32:49.057
We know. You're the one who negotiated
us up 5% on the McCutching deal.

32:49.082 --> 32:50.549
[Both laugh]

32:53.242 --> 32:56.945
I bet they think they
have the golden touch.

32:56.970 --> 32:58.604
It sure seems that way, doesn't it?

33:00.155 --> 33:01.655
All: [Chanting] Chug!
Chug! Chug! Chug! Chug!

33:01.680 --> 33:04.432
Chug! Chug! Chug! Chug! Chug! Chug!

33:04.949 --> 33:06.725
Ahh! $400 a bottle?

33:06.835 --> 33:08.836
Hell, I'm worth it. [Chuckles]

33:08.887 --> 33:10.938
Today, you're all worth it!

33:10.973 --> 33:13.107
Give me a case of Cristal, sweetness.

33:13.132 --> 33:14.957
Tip: You win the lottery, LaFramboise?

33:15.327 --> 33:16.911
It's not a crime to put some money

33:16.969 --> 33:18.262
back in the local economy, sheriff.

33:18.287 --> 33:19.838
No, it's definitely not a crime.

33:20.065 --> 33:22.966
Why don't you take a look at
these photographs right here?

33:22.991 --> 33:25.743
[Indistinct conversations]

33:25.768 --> 33:29.434
And I want you to tell me if
you think <i> that</i> is a crime.

33:31.091 --> 33:33.025
'Cause I think it is.

33:35.647 --> 33:38.382
Cody: I can't believe this!

33:38.417 --> 33:39.884
Seriously?! That's amazing!

33:39.918 --> 33:42.136
I think it's closer to 150 meals.

33:42.187 --> 33:43.437
In an hour!

33:43.462 --> 33:45.396
We're out of red chilies.
I'll get some from the van.

33:45.421 --> 33:46.754
Hey, babe, come on.

33:46.743 --> 33:47.875
Hap says we're almost
there. Let's go. Okay.

33:47.926 --> 33:49.877
I'll be back, partner.

33:50.621 --> 33:52.282
I need another special!

33:52.307 --> 33:54.325
One special... all day.

34:01.664 --> 34:03.004
Hey, uh...

34:03.605 --> 34:04.755
You got something.

34:07.532 --> 34:09.166
Thank you.

34:11.366 --> 34:13.300
[Sighs]

34:20.958 --> 34:22.176
Hey.

34:23.262 --> 34:25.971
Ada's married... <i>Happily</i> married.

34:25.996 --> 34:27.949
- I know that.
- Do you?

34:27.974 --> 34:30.168
Because you flirt... A lot.

34:30.301 --> 34:32.353
[Sighs] I don't want you
messing things up around here

34:32.404 --> 34:34.237
for any of us, so...

34:34.272 --> 34:36.567
Keep it professional, got it?

34:36.592 --> 34:37.956
Got it.

34:37.982 --> 34:40.484
Strictly professional, darlin'.

34:47.414 --> 34:50.366
♪

34:51.177 --> 34:53.027
Man: 20 feet!

34:53.313 --> 34:54.781
It's really happening?

34:54.909 --> 34:56.076
Yes, sir.

34:56.078 --> 34:57.244
[Chuckles]

34:57.246 --> 34:58.729
Kind of like watching
your dreams come to life,

34:58.763 --> 34:59.980
isn't it?

35:00.014 --> 35:01.348
It never gets old.

35:01.350 --> 35:02.683
Man: 10 feet!

35:02.685 --> 35:03.817
Hey, come on.

35:04.226 --> 35:06.177
2 feet!

35:07.824 --> 35:09.325
This is it!

35:15.246 --> 35:17.014
[Cheers and applause]

35:17.048 --> 35:19.182
Aah!

35:19.217 --> 35:21.018
[Cheers and applause continue]

35:21.069 --> 35:22.603
[Laughs]

35:22.654 --> 35:27.791
[Cheers and applause]

35:27.842 --> 35:29.059
[Laughs]

35:29.093 --> 35:30.560
Aren't you glad I
decided to invest in this?

35:31.086 --> 35:32.937
- Oh, you did?
- Yeah, right.

35:41.885 --> 35:43.969
Isn't it supposed to keep going?

35:44.092 --> 35:45.959
[Sighing] Yeah.

35:45.961 --> 35:47.627
[Sighs]

35:47.652 --> 35:49.487
It is.

35:51.572 --> 35:52.773
Hap?

35:52.798 --> 35:55.332
Why'd it stop?

35:55.357 --> 35:56.824
What happened?

36:03.801 --> 36:05.269
Billy: What the hell happened?

36:05.294 --> 36:06.494
Why'd it... why'd it stop?

36:06.519 --> 36:07.836
It was a spike hit.

36:07.861 --> 36:09.793
A-a spike? A... what's that?

36:09.818 --> 36:11.802
It's a little pool of oil under pressure.

36:12.464 --> 36:14.778
A little bit pokes through,
and it makes a little spout.

36:14.803 --> 36:16.520
That's it.

36:16.545 --> 36:17.903
That... what do you mean that's it?

36:17.928 --> 36:19.178
That's... There's no more oil?

36:20.506 --> 36:22.543
Not today.

36:23.025 --> 36:25.076
Go ahead and cap it, Tommy. Yes, sir.

36:25.745 --> 36:27.528
Hey, hey, hey, w-w-what
about our investment?

36:27.553 --> 36:31.239
Oh, well, yeah, that's
a... That's a tough break.

36:31.574 --> 36:35.137
But we'll use the money
and continue to drill and...

36:35.219 --> 36:36.937
Push deeper.

36:37.151 --> 36:38.335
Maybe in a few years,

36:38.360 --> 36:39.994
this well might produce something yet.

36:41.669 --> 36:42.836
Ah, damn it.

36:42.861 --> 36:44.328
You knew this well was a dud, didn't you?

36:44.353 --> 36:46.271
All that B.S. about
Wick and the investors...

36:46.296 --> 36:48.230
You played me.

36:52.067 --> 36:54.835
<i>You</i> asked <i> me</i> to
get in on this deal, remember?

36:54.869 --> 36:55.920
Yeah, because...

36:55.954 --> 36:57.221
You promised me it was gonna be a hit.

36:57.272 --> 36:58.939
Not every well is a gusher.

36:58.974 --> 37:00.958
Sometimes you drill a dry hole,

37:00.992 --> 37:02.760
but that's not on me.

37:02.794 --> 37:04.395
That's reality.

37:05.286 --> 37:06.953
When you met me,

37:06.978 --> 37:09.403
you told me you wanted
to learn the oil business.

37:09.481 --> 37:10.931
Well, guess what, son?

37:11.480 --> 37:12.713
You just learned.

37:13.523 --> 37:16.458
♪

37:19.262 --> 37:21.414
[Sighing]

37:23.952 --> 37:26.120
The samples I tested were negative.

37:26.327 --> 37:28.711
I'm sorry. If you can't deliver on this,

37:28.736 --> 37:31.003
- there are others who can, Ahmed.
- No.

37:31.028 --> 37:32.628
I'll give them what they want.

37:39.481 --> 37:41.816
I have another way in.

37:41.841 --> 37:43.878
You used me, pop!

37:44.255 --> 37:46.598
You... Said that Koala 1 was our well...

37:46.623 --> 37:48.262
The one that we drill together!

37:49.997 --> 37:52.765
It was our well. [Scoffs]

37:52.790 --> 37:54.491
Then about six weeks ago,

37:54.516 --> 37:56.934
I discovered that it might be dry.

37:57.239 --> 38:00.582
I wasn't for certain until today.

38:00.607 --> 38:02.525
Damn right I used you.

38:02.639 --> 38:05.024
I needed to get McCutching back.

38:05.049 --> 38:07.250
That's the prize.

38:08.529 --> 38:11.231
[Sighs] A trillion dollars' worth of oil.

38:12.221 --> 38:14.122
Billy had no business
having that in his hands

38:14.147 --> 38:15.163
in the first place.

38:16.537 --> 38:18.856
So, why didn't you just say that before?

38:20.112 --> 38:22.480
[Sighs]

38:22.505 --> 38:25.567
We've left a lot of blood
on the floor, you and me.

38:27.440 --> 38:29.791
I didn't always have time to teach you,

38:29.816 --> 38:32.584
and you damn sure didn't want to learn.

38:32.859 --> 38:34.676
But you impressed me today...

38:35.273 --> 38:36.307
With Billy.

38:36.896 --> 38:38.317
You were the bigger man.

38:39.816 --> 38:42.017
And I know you didn't want to do it,

38:42.042 --> 38:43.876
but you did it for me.

38:46.733 --> 38:49.785
Well, now it really is
time for me to teach you.

38:52.325 --> 38:55.393
I want you as my partner
on the McCutching play.

38:57.203 --> 39:00.338
<i>That's</i> the one we do together.

39:03.121 --> 39:04.221
Pop, I want that.

39:04.246 --> 39:05.697
I want that more than
anything in the world.

39:05.722 --> 39:06.888
You know that.

39:14.569 --> 39:17.037
We're gonna achieve great things together.

39:18.729 --> 39:21.246
[Chuckles]

39:21.529 --> 39:23.097
One thing, Wick.

39:23.122 --> 39:25.004
If you're gonna be in this with me...

39:26.202 --> 39:28.470
I mean,<i> really</i> in this...

39:28.495 --> 39:30.379
You got to stay focused.

39:30.404 --> 39:34.574
Yeah, of course. You've got
to eat, drink, and sleep oil.

39:34.599 --> 39:37.033
When you go to bed at night,
you got to dream about oil.

39:37.058 --> 39:38.440
When you rise in the morning,

39:38.465 --> 39:39.965
you got to be thinking about oil.

39:39.990 --> 39:41.274
You can't let anything...

39:41.299 --> 39:44.401
Not a woman, not even a good woman...

39:44.426 --> 39:46.994
Pull your eyes from the prize.

39:49.218 --> 39:51.135
Wait a minute. What are you...

39:51.303 --> 39:52.303
What are you saying?

39:53.280 --> 39:56.482
You got to end it with Jules... now.

39:56.993 --> 39:58.693
[Chuckles]

39:59.706 --> 40:02.641
♪

40:11.026 --> 40:13.311
Get some rest.

40:13.932 --> 40:15.599
Big day tomorrow.

40:22.028 --> 40:26.398
[Cellphone ringing]

40:28.306 --> 40:29.973
Wick: What? We got a problem.

40:30.843 --> 40:32.060
I got popped for boosting the oil.

40:32.085 --> 40:33.219
You got to get me out of here.

40:33.244 --> 40:34.551
Well, w-where are you?

40:34.576 --> 40:35.676
I'm in jail.

40:35.701 --> 40:36.968
The sheriff thinks I had something to do

40:36.993 --> 40:38.978
with Spinks' murder.

40:39.234 --> 40:40.317
Are you listening?

40:40.342 --> 40:42.427
They're gonna want me to flip,

40:42.452 --> 40:44.854
and you know what'll happen if I do.

40:44.879 --> 40:47.848
♪

40:49.424 --> 40:51.592
[Crickets chirping]

40:51.617 --> 40:53.168
Billy: [Sighs]

40:53.344 --> 40:55.312
I can't believe I was so...

40:55.337 --> 40:56.863
So stupid.

40:59.088 --> 41:00.473
I lost all of it.

41:01.748 --> 41:05.801
We have a house and a food truck.

41:05.826 --> 41:07.911
Kess and Ada make some damn good chicken.

41:08.617 --> 41:09.617
[Chuckles]

41:11.179 --> 41:12.346
[Sighs]

41:12.371 --> 41:13.871
It's you and me, Billy.

41:13.896 --> 41:15.832
That's what... That's what counts.

41:17.011 --> 41:19.059
[Sighs] You and the baby...

41:19.084 --> 41:21.119
Our family...

41:21.144 --> 41:23.261
Will never want for anything.

41:27.807 --> 41:29.758
[Sighs]

41:29.783 --> 41:32.885
I did not see this coming today.

41:33.395 --> 41:34.684
But you know what?

41:34.709 --> 41:35.723
When the time comes,

41:37.061 --> 41:38.812
neither will Hap Briggs.

